1
00:01:33,320 --> 00:01:34,240
Why did you call me here?

2
00:01:34,440 --> 00:01:34,960
Well, um...

3
00:01:34,960 --> 00:01:36,920
It's because their price was too high,

4
00:01:36,920 --> 00:01:39,200
so I didn't dare take too big a share.

5
00:01:39,480 --> 00:01:41,400
If the chairman asks about it, could you...

6
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:45,400
How much higher than the chairman's price?

7
00:01:48,080 --> 00:01:49,800
Way, way higher.

8
00:01:51,520 --> 00:01:52,320
Don't worry.

9
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:54,120
I'll make it worth your while.

10
00:01:54,520 --> 00:01:56,160
I know how to explain it to the chairman.

11
00:01:57,800 --> 00:01:58,640
Thank you.

12
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:00,320
Thank you, Director Xin.

13
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:03,840
Sister Xin,

14
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:06,120
how do you plan to explain it to the chairman?

15
00:02:08,039 --> 00:02:09,919
The chairman himself got greedy.

16
00:02:10,039 --> 00:02:10,840
This whole thing

17
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:12,600
should just be a lesson for them.

18
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:15,720
But Dayazhai's business still has to continue.

19
00:02:16,440 --> 00:02:17,880
For the missing share,

20
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:19,280
I'll go talk to Xuan Yan.

21
00:02:19,760 --> 00:02:21,560
After all, we had an agreement before.

22
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:23,120
Given his character, he won't back out.

23
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:25,600
About Vice President Zhang...

24
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:29,040
He's an old-timer by the chairman's side.

25
00:02:29,040 --> 00:02:30,760
Though he's incompetent in both conduct and work,

26
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:33,960
he's always been loyal to the chairman.

27
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:36,640
The chairman trusts his words a bit too much.

28
00:02:36,920 --> 00:02:37,760
I understand.

29
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:39,360
Sister Xin,

30
00:02:39,640 --> 00:02:40,560
being stuck in the middle,

31
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:42,080
it's really not easy for you.

32
00:02:42,640 --> 00:02:44,760
I just don't have any way out, that's all.

33
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:54,640
Actually, this IV drip,

34
00:02:54,920 --> 00:02:57,400
we could get it done in Taohua Town too.

35
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:00,400
Go ask about it.

36
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:02,200
When can we be discharged?

37
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:03,640
The doctor said

38
00:03:03,720 --> 00:03:05,080
at least three days.

39
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:17,000
Xuan paper's origin, Jing County.

40
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,280
A family of Xuan paper makers,

41
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:20,080
the 35th generation heir of the Xuan family,

42
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:21,800
Xuan Yongnian's rare paper.

43
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:22,720
Recently released,

44
00:03:22,720 --> 00:03:24,640
it has sparked a fierce buying frenzy.

45
00:03:24,920 --> 00:03:26,160
Recently, the rare paper on the market...

46
00:03:26,160 --> 00:03:26,600
What?

47
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:27,840
has caused a huge uproar.

48
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:29,680
Many buyers are flocking in for it.

49
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:31,160
What on earth is this?

50
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:34,120
When did I ever sell rare paper?

51
00:03:35,080 --> 00:03:36,840
People online are saying all kinds of things.

52
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:38,040
Isn't this spreading rumors?

53
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:39,160
Yes, it's rumors.

54
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:40,800
How can you believe it?

55
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:42,160
Quick, quick, lie down.

56
00:03:42,160 --> 00:03:44,480
I'm telling you, this is no small matter.

57
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:47,280
We need to call the police.

58
00:03:47,320 --> 00:03:49,160
We have to get some kind of answer.

59
00:03:49,160 --> 00:03:51,520
It's an online matter, who would you go to?

60
00:03:51,520 --> 00:03:52,240
Just lie down.

61
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:53,920
Your back isn't healed yet, come on.

62
00:03:53,920 --> 00:03:54,440
No, no.

63
00:03:54,440 --> 00:03:55,200
What are you doing?

64
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:56,360
We're going home.

65
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:57,640
Right now.

66
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:59,760
And he said it's in Taohua Town.

67
00:03:59,920 --> 00:04:01,240
We have to go back and check.

68
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:03,160
Why do you jump at every rumor you hear?

69
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:03,920
Lie down, I said.

70
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:05,520
What do you mean, jumping at rumors?

71
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:08,120
He's now doing this so blatantly.

72
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:10,200
I'm telling you, the consequences are serious.

73
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:12,240
He's going to ruin our Xuan family!

74
00:04:12,760 --> 00:04:14,360
Is it that serious? Lie down, lie down.

75
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:15,800
What are you doing? Your IV!

76
00:04:15,920 --> 00:04:16,959
I'm calling the doctor.

77
00:04:16,959 --> 00:04:18,160
Old Xuan, Old Xuan.

78
00:04:18,399 --> 00:04:19,680
What are you doing?

79
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:21,360
Home. We go now.

80
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:23,120
You can't.

81
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:30,640
You know about this.

82
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:31,200
I...

83
00:04:33,400 --> 00:04:34,440
Something happened at the factory?

84
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:36,120
Nothing's wrong. It's doing better than before.

85
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:36,680
Then...

86
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:42,360
Old Xuan.

87
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:49,800
Do you know how much Xuan Yan sold

88
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:51,240
our stockpiled paper for?

89
00:04:51,240 --> 00:04:52,800
Yes, over eight hundred thousand.

90
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:54,480
More than I expected.

91
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:56,040
I'd guessed around six hundred thousand.

92
00:04:57,520 --> 00:04:58,480
What's going on?

93
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:00,920
Over six million.

94
00:05:01,640 --> 00:05:03,080
Nearly seven million.

95
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:05,320
I haven't even done the math.

96
00:05:05,320 --> 00:05:06,400
But Old Xuan,

97
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:07,280
that much money

98
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:09,400
could keep the factory running for years.

99
00:05:09,640 --> 00:05:11,480
And enough for our retirement too.

100
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:12,280
Let me ask you.

101
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:15,200
You're saying Xuan Yan did this in my name?

102
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:21,160
Xuan Yan has sold out our Xuan ancestors!

103
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:21,920
Sold them out!

104
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:23,960
He sold me, Xuan Yongnian, out entirely!

105
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:24,920
Let's go home.

106
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:26,360
Old Xuan.

107
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:27,280
Old Xuan!

108
00:05:27,280 --> 00:05:28,200
Let's go home.

109
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:29,360
Old...

110
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:30,640
Yongnian!

111
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:33,200
Yongnian!

112
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:34,640
Our chairman

113
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:36,320
is very pleased with this.

114
00:05:36,320 --> 00:05:37,360
He said I handled things well,

115
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:38,920
protecting Dayazhai's interests.

116
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:41,080
So I'll borrow your tea

117
00:05:41,360 --> 00:05:42,680
to toast both of you.

118
00:05:42,920 --> 00:05:43,920
Thanks for your help.

119
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:44,400
Cheers.

120
00:05:50,640 --> 00:05:51,880
Hello, Xiaoman.

121
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,000
What is it? What's up?

122
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:54,880
Brother Xuan Yan, come back quick.

123
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:56,320
Why should I come back now?

124
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:58,360
Master's back from the hospital.

125
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:01,760
My... my dad's back?

126
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:03,880
Yes. Hurry back.

127
00:06:04,760 --> 00:06:05,760
Wait, does...

128
00:06:06,440 --> 00:06:08,520
Does he know about the rare paper?

129
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:10,880
Exactly, that's what this is about.

130
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:16,280
I'm done for.

131
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:23,000
Senior, take good care of your back this time.

132
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:23,560
Right.

133
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:24,800
No more scooping paper.

134
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:26,360
Feeling better?

135
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:27,520
Rest up well.

136
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:28,440
Master, it's good you're back.

137
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:33,120
Dad.

138
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:40,360
Dad.

139
00:06:40,880 --> 00:06:42,880
This isn't anyone else's fault.

140
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:44,880
I was the one who was wrong.

141
00:06:44,880 --> 00:06:46,400
If you have to blame someone, blame me.

142
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:49,200
Your father is already dead.

143
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:50,240
Old Xuan!

144
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:51,200
Dad!

145
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:53,880
You explain it to me clearly.

146
00:06:55,760 --> 00:06:57,440
How did you sell it for so much money?

147
00:06:57,800 --> 00:06:58,600
I... I...

148
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:06,440
Dad.

149
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:08,480
This is outrageous!

150
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:14,240
Yongnian.

151
00:07:15,080 --> 00:07:17,640
About what Xuan Yan did, I know.

152
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:19,560
And I agree with him.

153
00:07:22,640 --> 00:07:24,200
Have you lost your mind in your old age?

154
00:07:24,560 --> 00:07:26,080
You're the one being foolish.

155
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:29,920
Xuan Yan meant well.

156
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:33,200
He doesn't want our Xuan family's paper mill to fail.

157
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:35,920
He doesn't want you, his father, with a bad back,

158
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:37,560
still working the paper vats.

159
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:39,120
He cares about you.

160
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:40,760
That's right, old Xuan.

161
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:42,520
The way I see it,

162
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,200
Xuan Yan, this boy,

163
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:45,480
he didn't do anything really wrong.

164
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:46,880
With your back the way it is now,

165
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,120
can you still make paper?

166
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:49,600
Since you can't make paper,

167
00:07:49,880 --> 00:07:52,000
you might as well take what you made before

168
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:53,760
and sell it as rare paper at a high price.

169
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:56,120
It solves the mill's money problems.

170
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:58,440
Isn't that a good thing? Right?

171
00:07:58,520 --> 00:07:59,120
Exactly.

172
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:00,200
Honestly, what he's saying

173
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:01,400
makes perfect sense, doesn't it?

174
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:02,240
Yes.

175
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:09,200
So it seems you all support him.

176
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:11,280
You all agree with him.

177
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:12,800
Is that it?

178
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:15,760
We're agreeing with you!

179
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:17,680
You get to relax at home every day,

180
00:08:18,360 --> 00:08:20,080
without a single worry.

181
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:21,360
And as for us?

182
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:23,680
We don't have to worry about the mill closing.

183
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:26,560
We can keep working for the Xuan family.

184
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:27,280
Right?

185
00:08:27,280 --> 00:08:28,120
Yes, that's right.

186
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:29,200
Old Xuan.

187
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:30,000
Master.

188
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:31,640
If Brother Xuan Yan were being reckless,

189
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:32,760
we'd all scold him.

190
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,480
But he didn't do anything wrong.

191
00:08:34,880 --> 00:08:36,240
He did it for the good of the Xuan family,

192
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:37,559
for the good of the paper mill,

193
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:39,280
and most of all for your health.

194
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:40,760
That's right.

195
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,200
Do you all realize?

196
00:08:44,640 --> 00:08:45,920
What this kid did

197
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:50,360
was sell out me and our Xuan family's

198
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:51,640
thousand-year legacy completely!

199
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:53,800
Brother, why talk about death?

200
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:55,560
It's just a figure of speech.

201
00:08:55,640 --> 00:08:57,240
Look, Xuan Yan made all that money,

202
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:58,600
and didn't keep a single cent for himself.

203
00:08:58,600 --> 00:08:59,360
That money

204
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:01,280
all ended up in your pocket.

205
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:02,000
Right.

206
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,000
That's right, master.

207
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:05,240
Brother Xuan Yan isn't being unfilial, right?

208
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:06,320
If he really were unfilial,

209
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:08,000
wouldn't he wait until you were dead?

210
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:08,760
No, wait,

211
00:09:09,280 --> 00:09:10,240
that's not what I meant.

212
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,920
I mean he's not trying to cheat his dad, right?

213
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:13,760
He never intended to cheat you, right?

214
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:25,000
Dad.

215
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:28,520
I don't want to see you get hurt again.

216
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:31,360
I don't want you

217
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,280
having so many worries,

218
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:35,680
carrying so much on your mind.

219
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:38,600
As long as you can enjoy your later years in good health,

220
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:40,320
I'll do whatever you ask.

221
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:43,320
Yes, in this matter,

222
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:44,920
I was in the wrong.

223
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:47,440
Blame me for not thinking it through.

224
00:09:48,680 --> 00:09:50,240
If you want to scold me or hit me,

225
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:51,880
I'll take it.

226
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:53,760
Even if you beat me to death,

227
00:09:53,760 --> 00:09:54,520
I'll accept it.

228
00:09:54,880 --> 00:09:55,760
These words,

229
00:09:56,560 --> 00:09:58,640
I already said them to Mom back at the hospital.

230
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:08,560
All right, all right.

231
00:10:08,560 --> 00:10:09,120
Get up.

232
00:10:09,240 --> 00:10:10,360
Come on, get up.

233
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:12,280
Come, brother.

234
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:13,520
Up, up, up.

235
00:10:20,640 --> 00:10:21,480
Old Xuan.

236
00:10:23,880 --> 00:10:26,960
In the past, however harshly you treated this boy,

237
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:28,600
however much you scolded him,

238
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:30,280
I never said a word against it.

239
00:10:30,760 --> 00:10:32,600
But this time is different.

240
00:10:33,240 --> 00:10:35,880
He did it for the sake of our mill.

241
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:38,760
Think about it carefully now.

242
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:41,640
If he hadn't sold it for so much money,

243
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:44,080
wouldn't the mill have gone under?

244
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:46,880
And if the mill went under,

245
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:51,360
wouldn't it be the end of you?

246
00:10:52,760 --> 00:10:53,520
Mom.

247
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:10,960
I get it. I can see it too.

248
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:11,920
As for all of you,

249
00:11:13,760 --> 00:11:15,840
you're all singing the same tune as him.

250
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:17,520
Speaking with one voice.

251
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:18,520
No.

252
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:21,640
Master, I've never agreed with this.

253
00:11:21,880 --> 00:11:24,280
Alright, Zhang Du, speak up.

254
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:29,840
I just want to ask everyone one question.

255
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:32,120
The Xuan family, a millennium old,

256
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:34,360
passed down to this day,

257
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:35,880
what has it truly relied on?

258
00:11:39,160 --> 00:11:40,480
Look at him showing off.

259
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:43,840
It relied on the 108 papermaking steps,

260
00:11:43,840 --> 00:11:45,480
done with meticulous craftsmanship.

261
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:48,000
It relied on integrity with customers,

262
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:49,240
where a promise is worth a fortune.

263
00:11:50,360 --> 00:11:51,720
If our ancestors

264
00:11:51,760 --> 00:11:53,880
had cut corners like all of you,

265
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:55,640
would there even be a Xuan family today?

266
00:11:56,920 --> 00:11:58,200
Oh, so only you understand, huh?

267
00:11:58,960 --> 00:12:00,600
You're just thinking about the short term.

268
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:01,840
Enough.

269
00:12:03,880 --> 00:12:05,240
I know that all these years,

270
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:07,000
following me, Xuan Yongnian,

271
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:09,240
you've all truly suffered poverty.

272
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:13,080
Perhaps you're scared of being poor.

273
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:15,960
Perhaps you just want to make money.

274
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:18,360
Wanting to make money isn't wrong.

275
00:12:18,960 --> 00:12:19,880
But,

276
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:21,840
like some factories in town,

277
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:24,360
they'd blur right and wrong for money,

278
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:25,640
throwing away all shame.

279
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:28,360
Yongnian,

280
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:31,360
where did that come from?

281
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:35,520
Our Xuan family's millennium legacy

282
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:40,960
values honesty and trust.

283
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:42,640
Rather lose a fortune

284
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:44,360
than break a promise.

285
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:46,520
No matter how hard or tiring,

286
00:12:47,520 --> 00:12:48,480
never skip a single step.

287
00:12:50,920 --> 00:12:52,160
I, Xuan Yongnian, am not dead yet,

288
00:12:54,760 --> 00:12:55,640
and you, Xuan Yan,

289
00:12:56,280 --> 00:12:58,920
had the audacity to openly

290
00:12:59,960 --> 00:13:02,840
take my rare paper

291
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:05,120
and flaunt it all over the world.

292
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:08,880
Even hyping it up for huge profits.

293
00:13:09,760 --> 00:13:11,000
What are you trying to do?

294
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:13,480
Let your mother speak.

295
00:13:13,760 --> 00:13:15,080
Let everyone speak.

296
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:17,040
Isn't this forsaking your ancestors?

297
00:13:17,040 --> 00:13:19,400
Isn't this disgracing our forefathers?

298
00:13:21,120 --> 00:13:23,160
Yongnian, that's too harsh.

299
00:13:23,160 --> 00:13:24,120
It's not too harsh.

300
00:13:24,760 --> 00:13:26,200
The Xuan family legacy

301
00:13:27,360 --> 00:13:29,520
is all recorded in the records.

302
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:30,920
Among my ancestors,

303
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:33,760
the second branch's heir, Xuan Maoshi,

304
00:13:33,760 --> 00:13:35,520
there was a wealthy man named He.

305
00:13:36,160 --> 00:13:37,880
He didn't know Xuan paper,

306
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:40,760
so Xuan Maoshi charged a high price

307
00:13:40,880 --> 00:13:43,240
and sold him two reams of paper.

308
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:45,360
Just because of that,

309
00:13:45,840 --> 00:13:47,720
his position as heir

310
00:13:48,120 --> 00:13:49,280
was stripped away.

311
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:51,840
Also, my grandfather,

312
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:53,360
when he was young,

313
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:57,480
mistakenly sold a wrong ream to a customer.

314
00:13:57,640 --> 00:13:59,240
And that ream of paper, to this day,

315
00:13:59,240 --> 00:14:01,640
still sits under that chest in the study.

316
00:14:01,640 --> 00:14:02,960
Over seventy years have passed,

317
00:14:02,960 --> 00:14:05,920
still waiting for that person to claim it.

318
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:09,360
Xuan Yan,

319
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:13,640
for cutting corners at the drying yard,

320
00:14:13,640 --> 00:14:14,760
I struck you.

321
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:16,520
But now,

322
00:14:16,840 --> 00:14:19,200
you've still pulled off such an outrageous stunt.

323
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:22,080
Clearly, you haven't changed at all.

324
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:24,920
The Xuan family's ancestral code states clearly:

325
00:14:25,280 --> 00:14:26,760
Making Xuan paper takes 108 steps,

326
00:14:26,760 --> 00:14:28,160
each with its own secret.

327
00:14:28,760 --> 00:14:30,160
Rather sever ten fingers

328
00:14:30,280 --> 00:14:31,280
than lose a single skill.

329
00:14:31,520 --> 00:14:32,840
Rather have no heirs

330
00:14:34,120 --> 00:14:35,280
than pass it to the unworthy.

331
00:14:42,880 --> 00:14:43,720
Son.

332
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:46,480
Don't ever do this again.

333
00:14:49,480 --> 00:14:51,080
Say something back to your dad.

334
00:14:58,000 --> 00:14:58,760
Xuan Yan.

335
00:15:02,520 --> 00:15:04,520
If you were even half as steady

336
00:15:05,160 --> 00:15:07,200
as Zhang Du,

337
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:09,640
I'd feel at ease.

338
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:10,880
But fine, this works too.

339
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:15,200
You don't care about being the Xuan family heir anyway.

340
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:17,240
Fine, fine.

341
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:18,000
That way,

342
00:15:18,240 --> 00:15:21,240
I won't have to agonize over it anymore.

343
00:15:22,760 --> 00:15:23,600
Yongnian.

344
00:15:24,120 --> 00:15:25,160
Please, calm down a bit.

345
00:15:25,160 --> 00:15:26,240
Stay out of this.

346
00:15:26,920 --> 00:15:27,720
Xuan Yan.

347
00:15:28,640 --> 00:15:29,760
From now on,

348
00:15:29,760 --> 00:15:32,360
go and do your little cultural products thing.

349
00:15:32,480 --> 00:15:33,840
Whether you succeed or fail,

350
00:15:33,840 --> 00:15:35,160
it has nothing to do with the Xuan family.

351
00:15:35,160 --> 00:15:37,160
And whatever happens to the Xuan family,

352
00:15:37,160 --> 00:15:40,080
has absolutely nothing to do with you.

353
00:15:49,880 --> 00:15:50,400
Master.

354
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:51,080
Calm down, please.

355
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:51,880
Don't act rashly.

356
00:15:51,880 --> 00:15:52,640
Master.

357
00:15:54,080 --> 00:15:55,200
What are you saying?

358
00:15:55,400 --> 00:15:57,360
Answer your dad, son.

359
00:15:57,640 --> 00:15:58,720
Say something to your dad.

360
00:15:59,000 --> 00:15:59,840
Son.

361
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:04,280
Just answer him, son.

362
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:09,760
Dad,

363
00:16:12,760 --> 00:16:15,600
I don't know just how good

364
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:18,240
your ideal heir is supposed to be.

365
00:16:18,760 --> 00:16:20,200
But in all my years,

366
00:16:22,280 --> 00:16:24,360
for every right thing I've ever done,

367
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:27,360
you've never once praised me.

368
00:16:38,160 --> 00:16:38,960
Dad,

369
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:44,840
since you've said all this today,

370
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:47,480
then I'll just say one thing.

371
00:16:49,520 --> 00:16:50,920
Whether you approve of me or not,

372
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:53,600
I really don't care.

373
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:55,000
Don't say that, son.

374
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:56,120
Say something to your dad.

375
00:16:56,120 --> 00:16:56,520
Xuan Yan.

376
00:16:56,520 --> 00:16:58,000
Answer your dad, come on.

377
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,840
Xuan Yan, Xuan Yan, Brother Xuan Yan.

378
00:16:59,920 --> 00:17:02,400
Just say something back to your dad.

379
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:03,160
Big brother.

380
00:17:03,160 --> 00:17:05,520
Answer your dad, please.

381
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:07,520
He won't back down either.

382
00:17:07,760 --> 00:17:08,520
Old Xuan.

383
00:17:08,960 --> 00:17:11,079
Say something to your dad.

384
00:17:11,079 --> 00:17:12,000
Let him go.

385
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:54,520
Treat materials as you would your parents

386
00:17:54,760 --> 00:17:55,840
Do not waste heaven's gifts

387
00:17:55,840 --> 00:17:57,360
Treat materials as you would your parents

388
00:17:57,520 --> 00:17:58,640
Do not waste heaven's gifts

389
00:17:58,640 --> 00:17:59,360
Say it again

390
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:00,840
Treat materials as you would your parents

391
00:18:00,880 --> 00:18:02,360
Do not waste heaven's gifts

392
00:18:02,360 --> 00:18:03,840
Craft with reverence

393
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:05,360
Do not disgrace our ancestors' craft

394
00:18:05,360 --> 00:18:05,520
Say it

395
00:18:05,520 --> 00:18:06,960
Craft with reverence

396
00:18:07,080 --> 00:18:08,520
Do not disgrace our ancestors' craft

397
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:09,360
Say it again

398
00:18:09,360 --> 00:18:10,840
Craft with reverence

399
00:18:11,120 --> 00:18:12,600
Do not disgrace our ancestors' craft

400
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:13,760
Will you dare burn the straw for fire again?

401
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:14,480
Will you dare or not?

402
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:15,360
I won't dare anymore

403
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:17,080
Will you dare bathe in the paper vat again?

404
00:18:17,640 --> 00:18:18,520
Will you dare or not?

405
00:18:18,640 --> 00:18:19,520
I won't dare anymore

406
00:18:19,840 --> 00:18:21,720
That'll teach you to bathe! Take that!

407
00:18:21,720 --> 00:18:22,840
Jumping in the paper vat water

408
00:18:24,200 --> 00:18:25,120
That'll teach you to burn the straw!

409
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:25,880
I won't dare anymore

410
00:19:03,160 --> 00:19:04,240
You can't touch that.

411
00:19:05,680 --> 00:19:06,680
What are you doing here?

412
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,240
Where's Xuan Yan?

413
00:19:09,160 --> 00:19:10,560
Is his motorcycle outside?

414
00:19:10,640 --> 00:19:11,440
It's not.

415
00:19:11,520 --> 00:19:13,480
Then he must be out, not at home.

416
00:19:13,560 --> 00:19:14,280
Have a seat first.

417
00:19:14,280 --> 00:19:15,320
Let me make you some tea.

418
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:16,560
It's fine, don't bother.

419
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:19,480
So where could he have gone?

420
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:21,280
If you ask me,

421
00:19:21,400 --> 00:19:22,960
don't worry too much about him.

422
00:19:23,440 --> 00:19:25,560
Pitiful people always have their faults.

423
00:19:26,160 --> 00:19:27,240
After going through this,

424
00:19:27,480 --> 00:19:30,000
letting him reflect on it is a good thing.

425
00:19:30,080 --> 00:19:32,000
I actually think Xuan Yan did nothing wrong.

426
00:19:32,240 --> 00:19:33,440
It's Uncle Xuan.

427
00:19:33,600 --> 00:19:35,200
Uncle Xuan is being too harsh.

428
00:19:35,560 --> 00:19:38,000
The Xuan family has passed down for a thousand years.

429
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:40,440
For my master to still have such integrity and reverence,

430
00:19:40,440 --> 00:19:42,040
that's truly rare and precious.

431
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:43,720
If descendants are allowed to run wild,

432
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:45,520
they'd end up like Jiang Erhu's family.

433
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:47,600
Uncle Xuan is right.

434
00:19:47,600 --> 00:19:49,320
But Xuan Yan's situation is different.

435
00:19:49,320 --> 00:19:51,320
From start to finish, he wasn't doing it for himself.

436
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:53,960
I think it's understandable.

437
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:56,920
The sixth Xuan family precept:

438
00:19:57,600 --> 00:19:59,240
Do not envy silk and splendor.

439
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:00,720
Do not chase shortcuts to success.

440
00:20:00,720 --> 00:20:01,800
Uphold the principle of simplicity.

441
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:03,240
Okay, okay, enough.

442
00:20:03,240 --> 00:20:04,320
I'm done talking with you.

443
00:20:04,320 --> 00:20:06,160
You're just Uncle Xuan's spokesperson.

444
00:20:06,160 --> 00:20:07,040
I'm going to find him.

445
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:22,920
My mom told you I was here, right?

446
00:21:30,720 --> 00:21:32,160
Remember my master?

447
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:35,240
The one you snapped at.

448
00:21:36,280 --> 00:21:37,920
Can you talk nicely?

449
00:21:39,040 --> 00:21:40,480
The first time he taught me,

450
00:21:40,480 --> 00:21:41,840
he brought me right here.

451
00:21:42,040 --> 00:21:43,000
This place...

452
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:45,200
The scenery changes constantly,

453
00:21:45,240 --> 00:21:47,280
just like a person's mood.

454
00:21:47,280 --> 00:21:49,280
I still remember he told me

455
00:21:49,720 --> 00:21:50,800
one saying.

456
00:21:51,240 --> 00:21:54,280
If the mountain won't come to me, I'll go to it.

457
00:21:54,600 --> 00:21:55,840
Back then, I didn't get it.

458
00:21:56,320 --> 00:21:57,160
Later on,

459
00:21:58,200 --> 00:21:59,720
I started coming here often.

460
00:21:59,920 --> 00:22:00,840
Every time I come,

461
00:22:00,920 --> 00:22:02,480
my mood is different.

462
00:22:03,560 --> 00:22:04,560
Just like right now.

463
00:22:05,200 --> 00:22:06,000
Look.

464
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:08,080
Those mountains, one after another,

465
00:22:08,760 --> 00:22:11,720
aren't they like the challenges I have to face?

466
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:13,920
I really didn't expect

467
00:22:14,240 --> 00:22:16,240
someone as thick-skinned as you

468
00:22:16,680 --> 00:22:18,520
could actually feel sad sometimes.

469
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:22,920
Who said I was sad?

470
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:25,720
You're really something.

471
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:27,920
I'm not done talking and you're already imagining things.

472
00:22:28,160 --> 00:22:30,160
Have you been reading too many romance novels?

473
00:22:33,080 --> 00:22:34,960
Yes, yes, I read too many romance novels.

474
00:22:34,960 --> 00:22:35,840
So what?

475
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:43,560
Have you ever heard

476
00:22:43,560 --> 00:22:45,040
the legend about Liudao Bay?

477
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:47,960
They say beneath the cliffs of Liudao Bay,

478
00:22:47,960 --> 00:22:50,840
there's a stunning beauty who captivates souls.

479
00:22:51,080 --> 00:22:53,080
Whatever your wish, just jump down

480
00:22:53,160 --> 00:22:54,280
and she'll grant it.

481
00:22:54,280 --> 00:22:55,680
She'll make your dreams come true.

482
00:22:55,960 --> 00:22:57,240
Then hurry up and jump.

483
00:22:57,240 --> 00:22:58,280
Get her contact info while you're at it.

484
00:22:58,280 --> 00:22:59,560
The two of you can be together forever.

485
00:23:00,440 --> 00:23:02,160
If you could see him,

486
00:23:02,200 --> 00:23:03,480
he'd probably be a handsome guy.

487
00:23:04,320 --> 00:23:05,920
You're seriously messed up.

488
00:23:20,400 --> 00:23:21,440
Wait, what are you doing?

489
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:23,760
Xuan Yan!

490
00:23:24,480 --> 00:23:25,320
What are you doing?

491
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:26,600
Lin Yiran,

492
00:23:27,240 --> 00:23:29,240
I think I can see her.

493
00:23:35,640 --> 00:23:37,000
She's waving at me.

494
00:23:42,400 --> 00:23:43,520
She's so beautiful.

495
00:23:44,160 --> 00:23:44,960
Really.

496
00:23:45,760 --> 00:23:46,560
Prettier than you.

497
00:23:47,160 --> 00:23:48,000
She... she's prettier than me?

498
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:49,080
Get back here first!

499
00:23:49,080 --> 00:23:49,840
Xuan Yan!

500
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:51,000
Lin Yiran!

501
00:23:53,960 --> 00:23:54,960
Xuan Yan, I'm talking to you!

502
00:23:54,960 --> 00:23:56,080
Come back here first!

503
00:24:05,200 --> 00:24:06,000
Goodbye.

504
00:24:08,840 --> 00:24:10,000
Xuan Yan! Xuan Yan! Xuan...

505
00:24:10,240 --> 00:24:11,000
Xuan Yan!

506
00:24:13,800 --> 00:24:15,480
Xuan Yan! Xuan Yan! Xuan...

507
00:24:18,520 --> 00:24:19,280
How was it?

508
00:24:19,840 --> 00:24:20,640
Was I cool?

509
00:24:22,240 --> 00:24:23,480
Are you out of your mind?

510
00:24:24,640 --> 00:24:26,240
I came here to support you,

511
00:24:26,240 --> 00:24:27,280
to comfort you a bit.

512
00:24:27,560 --> 00:24:28,920
Your dad scolding you was totally deserved.

513
00:24:28,920 --> 00:24:30,520
I'm telling you, it wasn't enough.

514
00:24:30,520 --> 00:24:31,760
There's something wrong with your head.

515
00:24:32,040 --> 00:24:32,920
Come down here!

516
00:24:33,400 --> 00:24:34,600
The view is amazing.

517
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:36,000
Why would I come down?

518
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:37,320
You've got a screw loose.

519
00:24:40,080 --> 00:24:40,920
Come up here.

520
00:25:24,400 --> 00:25:25,520
Are we still fishing today or not?

521
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:27,560
Someone give me a straight answer.

522
00:25:33,720 --> 00:25:34,600
If you ask me,

523
00:25:34,840 --> 00:25:36,280
none of you should bother fishing.

524
00:25:36,440 --> 00:25:37,440
I don't want to bake in the sun either.

525
00:25:54,360 --> 00:25:55,160
Tell me,

526
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:57,440
Has Old Xuan

527
00:25:57,440 --> 00:25:58,800
completely lost his mind?

528
00:25:58,960 --> 00:26:00,760
He's naming Zhang Du as his successor.

529
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:02,360
Something this important,

530
00:26:02,720 --> 00:26:03,720
handled so carelessly.

531
00:26:03,760 --> 00:26:05,000
I think Xuan Yan is a hundred times better

532
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:06,240
than that Zhang Du, and then some.

533
00:26:06,640 --> 00:26:09,560
We watched Xuan Yan grow up.

534
00:26:09,560 --> 00:26:10,640
What kind of person he is,

535
00:26:10,640 --> 00:26:12,080
we all know very well.

536
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:13,720
Out of everyone here,

537
00:26:13,840 --> 00:26:15,960
Xuan Yan has the sincerest heart.

538
00:26:16,280 --> 00:26:18,760
Brother Xuan Yan is better than Zhang Du.

539
00:26:21,240 --> 00:26:22,280
Today,

540
00:26:22,400 --> 00:26:24,000
let me just say this straight out.

541
00:26:24,640 --> 00:26:27,400
Master Xuan, if he chooses Zhang Du,

542
00:26:27,520 --> 00:26:29,080
he'll suffer for it down the road.

543
00:26:29,920 --> 00:26:31,400
It's already come to this.

544
00:26:31,440 --> 00:26:33,080
What good does saying all this do?

545
00:26:33,280 --> 00:26:34,840
I just can't stand it.

546
00:26:35,280 --> 00:26:36,840
Xuan Yan, growing up,

547
00:26:36,840 --> 00:26:38,640
took so many beatings from his dad.

548
00:26:40,560 --> 00:26:42,080
If you don't want to work,

549
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:43,840
then everyone go home and rest.

550
00:26:44,160 --> 00:26:45,520
All this bickering here

551
00:26:45,600 --> 00:26:47,080
just makes everyone feel bad.

552
00:26:47,640 --> 00:26:48,440
Honestly.

553
00:26:50,720 --> 00:26:51,520
Let's go.

554
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:06,040
So this time you're driving Xuan Yan away.

555
00:27:06,440 --> 00:27:09,160
Nobody in the factory supports it.

556
00:27:13,240 --> 00:27:14,640
Su Lan, over this,

557
00:27:14,640 --> 00:27:15,760
even shed tears.

558
00:27:18,840 --> 00:27:20,080
After all, Xuan Yan

559
00:27:20,080 --> 00:27:21,520
grew up right before

560
00:27:21,760 --> 00:27:23,200
everyone's eyes.

561
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:25,200
Whether the kid is good or not,

562
00:27:26,560 --> 00:27:28,160
anyone can see clearly.

563
00:27:32,960 --> 00:27:34,280
I want to say to you,

564
00:27:34,640 --> 00:27:36,000
your heart is truly cold.

565
00:27:44,040 --> 00:27:45,560
Honestly, deep down,

566
00:27:48,800 --> 00:27:50,040
I'm suffering too.

567
00:27:53,800 --> 00:27:56,720
Are you really naming Zhang Du as your successor?

568
00:27:58,320 --> 00:27:59,360
Let's wait and see.

569
00:28:01,360 --> 00:28:02,760
Open your eyes wide

570
00:28:02,760 --> 00:28:04,200
and take a good long look.

571
00:28:09,560 --> 00:28:10,400
It's getting late.

572
00:28:10,400 --> 00:28:12,000
You should head home and rest too.

573
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:12,760
Why?

574
00:28:15,800 --> 00:28:18,040
I'll wait till Xiumei's asleep, then go back.

575
00:28:56,440 --> 00:28:57,440
Mr. Xuan,

576
00:28:57,600 --> 00:28:59,240
What do you think of this courtyard?

577
00:28:59,960 --> 00:29:01,920
I used to play here as a kid.

578
00:29:01,920 --> 00:29:03,040
Coming back now,

579
00:29:03,480 --> 00:29:04,720
it's still a delight to the eye.

580
00:29:05,240 --> 00:29:07,000
After all, this is a place

581
00:29:07,160 --> 00:29:08,600
where even Li Bai lingered on.

582
00:29:08,600 --> 00:29:09,560
Poets and scholars,

583
00:29:09,800 --> 00:29:11,240
a dream spanning a thousand years.

584
00:29:12,360 --> 00:29:13,520
Actually, to be honest,

585
00:29:13,520 --> 00:29:15,920
your family's old residence is quite nice.

586
00:29:15,960 --> 00:29:17,840
Just because you and your father had a fight,

587
00:29:17,840 --> 00:29:19,240
you insisted on moving out?

588
00:29:19,240 --> 00:29:21,320
My dad has already cut ties with me.

589
00:29:21,800 --> 00:29:23,240
I need to have some pride too.

590
00:29:23,240 --> 00:29:24,400
I can't just stay there.

591
00:29:24,960 --> 00:29:26,240
You're taking this quite seriously.

592
00:29:26,240 --> 00:29:27,760
Fathers and sons don't hold grudges overnight.

593
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:29,240
Alright.

594
00:29:29,240 --> 00:29:31,360
Then for lunch, I'll cook.

595
00:29:31,360 --> 00:29:33,480
I'll make you a couple of my signature dishes.

596
00:29:33,480 --> 00:29:34,920
Let you taste my cooking.

597
00:29:36,440 --> 00:29:37,800
Director Xin, you're too kind.

598
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:39,240
You deserve it.

599
00:29:41,040 --> 00:29:42,000
Mr. Xuan,

600
00:29:43,080 --> 00:29:45,680
are you satisfied with our collaboration?

601
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:46,840
Yes, I am.

602
00:29:47,680 --> 00:29:50,160
Production's great, sales are strong.

603
00:29:50,240 --> 00:29:51,040
Everything's going well.

604
00:29:51,800 --> 00:29:53,800
Hearing you're satisfied puts me at ease.

605
00:29:55,480 --> 00:29:58,600
But you and Lin Yiran really surprised me.

606
00:29:58,640 --> 00:30:00,240
I never expected

607
00:30:00,400 --> 00:30:03,400
you'd open up the Xuan wallpaper market.

608
00:30:04,560 --> 00:30:07,440
With you in Taohua Town's Xuan paper industry,

609
00:30:07,680 --> 00:30:09,000
we can truly see hope.

610
00:30:09,200 --> 00:30:10,520
Director Xin, you're mistaken.

611
00:30:10,800 --> 00:30:11,920
It's all of us.

612
00:30:12,560 --> 00:30:14,520
Together, we'll bring the Xuan paper industry

613
00:30:14,520 --> 00:30:16,240
into a brand new future.

614
00:30:16,440 --> 00:30:17,360
Let's work hard together.

615
00:30:18,640 --> 00:30:20,440
Since we share the same goal,

616
00:30:20,640 --> 00:30:21,920
from now on,

617
00:30:21,920 --> 00:30:24,160
we'll be in deep collaboration.

618
00:30:24,240 --> 00:30:26,600
You handle the inside, product development.

619
00:30:26,600 --> 00:30:29,000
I'll handle the outside, production and sales.

620
00:30:29,200 --> 00:30:30,520
As for the designer's fees,

621
00:30:30,520 --> 00:30:31,800
we'll pay you at the rate

622
00:30:31,800 --> 00:30:33,720
of top-tier domestic designers.

623
00:30:33,760 --> 00:30:35,040
As for this courtyard,

624
00:30:35,040 --> 00:30:36,320
I've rented it for five years.

625
00:30:36,440 --> 00:30:38,320
It'll serve as your studio.

626
00:30:38,640 --> 00:30:39,640
From now on,

627
00:30:39,640 --> 00:30:42,200
you just focus on designing great products.

628
00:30:42,200 --> 00:30:43,640
All the other trivial matters,

629
00:30:43,640 --> 00:30:45,000
leave them to me.

630
00:30:47,080 --> 00:30:48,200
Any other conditions?

631
00:30:48,800 --> 00:30:50,240
Don't hold back, just say it.

632
00:30:51,720 --> 00:30:53,480
Director Xin, you've thought of everything.

633
00:30:53,480 --> 00:30:55,080
If I raised any more conditions,

634
00:30:55,080 --> 00:30:56,720
wouldn't that be ungrateful?

635
00:31:12,720 --> 00:31:14,960
Work's exhausting, no money's stressful.

636
00:31:15,760 --> 00:31:16,880
Once you've got money,

637
00:31:18,280 --> 00:31:20,320
having nothing to do stresses you out too.

638
00:31:21,640 --> 00:31:24,200
Life just never gives you a break, does it?

639
00:31:27,840 --> 00:31:28,640
Look, look.

640
00:31:34,880 --> 00:31:35,320
Look at this.

641
00:31:36,600 --> 00:31:37,920
You're worse off than me.

642
00:31:40,160 --> 00:31:42,520
Since Xuan Yan bought me these glasses,

643
00:31:43,040 --> 00:31:44,240
my eyesight's

644
00:31:44,680 --> 00:31:46,800
even sharper than it was 20 years ago.

645
00:31:48,080 --> 00:31:50,160
I'm not trying to dig at you, though.

646
00:31:53,920 --> 00:31:55,600
You can't handle this delicate work.

647
00:31:56,160 --> 00:31:57,600
Go take a walk outside.

648
00:31:58,040 --> 00:32:00,800
You've got tons of free time now.

649
00:32:00,800 --> 00:32:03,720
Do whatever you feel like doing.

650
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:19,800
Okay

651
00:32:20,960 --> 00:32:22,000
Go ahead

652
00:32:50,360 --> 00:32:51,000
Hello, boss.

653
00:32:51,560 --> 00:32:52,480
Hello, boss.

654
00:32:53,920 --> 00:32:54,520
Old Xuan.

655
00:32:56,400 --> 00:32:57,200
Where's Magan?

656
00:32:57,920 --> 00:32:58,720
Who knows.

657
00:32:59,440 --> 00:33:01,360
Lazy donkeys always find excuses.

658
00:33:05,160 --> 00:33:05,960
You go.

659
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:07,800
What do you mean?

660
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:10,000
I'll handle the screen.

661
00:33:11,160 --> 00:33:12,840
Don't just stand there. Hurry up.

662
00:33:13,760 --> 00:33:14,440
But your back...

663
00:33:24,240 --> 00:33:24,960
Master.

664
00:33:25,560 --> 00:33:26,440
Master, Master.

665
00:33:27,160 --> 00:33:27,960
Master.

666
00:33:28,840 --> 00:33:30,560
Your back just healed.

667
00:33:30,640 --> 00:33:32,320
You need to rest more.

668
00:33:32,840 --> 00:33:33,760
No, no, Master, Master.

669
00:33:34,600 --> 00:33:35,720
The thing is, right now,

670
00:33:35,760 --> 00:33:36,920
even if you lift it,

671
00:33:36,920 --> 00:33:38,360
it wouldn't count as your work.

672
00:33:39,440 --> 00:33:40,640
Master, look at me.

673
00:33:40,640 --> 00:33:41,560
I can do it now.

674
00:33:41,760 --> 00:33:43,560
Let me handle the screen, Master.

675
00:33:44,360 --> 00:33:45,600
You rest. Just watch me.

676
00:33:45,720 --> 00:33:46,440
I'm ready now.

677
00:33:46,440 --> 00:33:47,080
Father.

678
00:33:47,480 --> 00:33:48,280
Today, with Master watching,

679
00:33:48,280 --> 00:33:49,160
I'll handle the screen.

680
00:33:49,440 --> 00:33:51,160
That's right, Master.

681
00:33:51,160 --> 00:33:53,080
Your back just healed. Take a rest.

682
00:33:53,160 --> 00:33:54,240
Have a rest, Master.

683
00:33:55,480 --> 00:33:58,800
Father, first screen, water hugs the body.

684
00:34:02,760 --> 00:34:03,560
Lift!

685
00:34:04,720 --> 00:34:06,440
Second screen, water breaks the core.

686
00:34:38,760 --> 00:34:39,400
Master.

687
00:34:41,080 --> 00:34:42,760
Zhang Du, come, have a seat.

688
00:34:42,840 --> 00:34:43,719
Okay.

689
00:34:44,920 --> 00:34:45,840
Is something on your mind?

690
00:34:47,360 --> 00:34:48,159
Master.

691
00:34:48,360 --> 00:34:49,159
I've been...

692
00:34:50,320 --> 00:34:51,639
having an idea.

693
00:34:52,199 --> 00:34:53,320
Alright, let's hear it.

694
00:34:53,600 --> 00:34:54,600
Just think about it.

695
00:34:54,719 --> 00:34:57,320
Our Xuan family ancestors, generation after generation,

696
00:34:57,320 --> 00:34:58,480
from ancient times till now,

697
00:34:58,520 --> 00:35:00,400
have made so many fine papers.

698
00:35:00,840 --> 00:35:03,760
I remember, among our paper samples,

699
00:35:03,760 --> 00:35:07,640
there's a Song Dynasty Chengxintang paper.

700
00:35:07,760 --> 00:35:08,280
Isn't there?

701
00:35:09,200 --> 00:35:09,800
Yes, there is.

702
00:35:10,720 --> 00:35:11,800
Just one sheet.

703
00:35:12,080 --> 00:35:16,200
I think it dates back to Southern Tang of the Five Dynasties.

704
00:35:17,040 --> 00:35:19,720
There was some emperor with the surname Li.

705
00:35:21,160 --> 00:35:22,000
Li Yu.

706
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:23,160
Yes, yes, that's right.

707
00:35:23,200 --> 00:35:24,600
I think his name was Li Yu.

708
00:35:25,360 --> 00:35:26,480
The great poet.

709
00:35:26,960 --> 00:35:29,440
The one who wrote "East wind swept the small tower again last night."

710
00:35:29,440 --> 00:35:31,200
I studied it back in school.

711
00:35:32,400 --> 00:35:34,160
I heard from the older generation

712
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:36,600
that this paper

713
00:35:37,440 --> 00:35:38,960
was made by him.

714
00:35:39,520 --> 00:35:42,120
He personally designed and supervised it.

715
00:35:42,440 --> 00:35:45,440
And it was named after his palace at that time,

716
00:35:45,440 --> 00:35:47,280
called Chengxintang.

717
00:35:47,280 --> 00:35:47,800
Right.

718
00:35:47,800 --> 00:35:49,280
That's naturally a fine paper.

719
00:35:49,960 --> 00:35:51,280
How could it not be?

720
00:35:51,480 --> 00:35:52,880
The king of papers.

721
00:35:54,000 --> 00:35:55,200
Its surface like an eggshell membrane,

722
00:35:55,800 --> 00:35:57,280
firm and pure as jade,

723
00:35:57,640 --> 00:35:59,040
light and thin as a wing.

724
00:35:59,480 --> 00:36:00,680
That's exactly what it's describing.

725
00:36:02,280 --> 00:36:05,080
In the Song Dynasty, it was priceless and rare.

726
00:36:05,520 --> 00:36:06,880
As for what still exists today,

727
00:36:07,600 --> 00:36:09,480
I think some museum has one sheet.

728
00:36:09,560 --> 00:36:13,120
I remember it's by the great Northern Song calligrapher

729
00:36:13,280 --> 00:36:15,640
Cai Xiang's "Chengxintang Paper Letter."

730
00:36:16,040 --> 00:36:18,040
And then there's this one in our Xuan family.

731
00:36:21,680 --> 00:36:23,680
Why are you bringing all this up?

732
00:36:24,680 --> 00:36:25,520
Master,

733
00:36:26,000 --> 00:36:28,560
why don't we recreate the Chengxintang paper?

734
00:36:29,040 --> 00:36:30,000
Just think about it.

735
00:36:30,280 --> 00:36:32,080
Ever since the last Paper King Contest,

736
00:36:32,120 --> 00:36:34,400
our Xuan family's reputation has taken a huge hit.

737
00:36:34,560 --> 00:36:36,560
If we can successfully recreate

738
00:36:36,560 --> 00:36:38,720
this long-lost king of papers,

739
00:36:39,120 --> 00:36:41,560
who could ever shake the Xuan family's standing?

740
00:36:49,200 --> 00:36:51,320
Easier said than done.

741
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:54,960
I know, it'll definitely be hard.

742
00:36:55,360 --> 00:36:56,640
But the good thing is,

743
00:36:57,000 --> 00:36:58,680
we have a sample to work from.

744
00:36:59,240 --> 00:37:01,640
We can study it against a proper standard.

745
00:37:02,320 --> 00:37:04,720
And you happen to have time now.

746
00:37:05,120 --> 00:37:06,440
The two of us, master and disciple,

747
00:37:06,520 --> 00:37:08,640
can put in the effort to grind an iron rod into a needle.

748
00:37:09,000 --> 00:37:11,840
Isn't that far more meaningful than scooping paper every day?

749
00:37:13,400 --> 00:37:15,280
This Xuan family Chengxintang paper

750
00:37:15,480 --> 00:37:17,680
was made by the Xuan family's ancestors.

751
00:37:18,440 --> 00:37:19,400
I remember

752
00:37:19,880 --> 00:37:22,880
there's a line of poetry on it.

753
00:37:23,640 --> 00:37:26,120
That line seems to be

754
00:37:26,640 --> 00:37:29,720
the ancestors' understanding of making this paper.

755
00:37:30,840 --> 00:37:32,600
What poem is it? Do you still remember?

756
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:34,920
Wait right here.

757
00:37:48,440 --> 00:37:51,880
A thousand pestles of jade marrow, sparking stardust

758
00:37:52,280 --> 00:37:55,360
One sheet of Chengxin paper reveals the void

759
00:37:58,440 --> 00:37:59,640
Do you understand?

760
00:38:01,920 --> 00:38:02,880
Not really.

761
00:38:03,360 --> 00:38:05,280
But it reminds me of

762
00:38:05,720 --> 00:38:08,880
a mystical state described in the Huainanzi.

763
00:38:10,400 --> 00:38:13,840
Clear the heart and mind, grasp the divide of heaven and man.

764
00:38:14,880 --> 00:38:15,880
I don't know either

765
00:38:16,440 --> 00:38:18,880
if there's any connection between them.

766
00:38:19,120 --> 00:38:20,320
What you're talking about,

767
00:38:20,640 --> 00:38:21,600
I don't get it either.

768
00:38:22,480 --> 00:38:23,840
Anyway, I just feel

769
00:38:24,280 --> 00:38:26,160
even if we grind an iron rod into a needle,

770
00:38:26,600 --> 00:38:28,520
it's still a waste of time.

771
00:38:31,360 --> 00:38:32,120
Master,

772
00:38:32,800 --> 00:38:34,200
I think we should give it a try.

773
00:38:37,880 --> 00:38:38,680
Alright.

774
00:38:40,640 --> 00:38:41,720
Then let's try.

775
00:38:44,120 --> 00:38:46,400
Whether or not we can make Chengxintang paper,

776
00:38:46,400 --> 00:38:48,960
today, you've inspired me.

777
00:38:49,280 --> 00:38:52,400
From now on, I'll have something to do.

778
00:38:54,040 --> 00:38:55,000
And besides,

779
00:38:55,440 --> 00:38:56,560
it's a chance

780
00:38:57,080 --> 00:38:59,800
to restore the glory of our Xuan ancestors.

781
00:39:00,440 --> 00:39:02,800
This matter is very important,

782
00:39:02,840 --> 00:39:04,000
and it's meaningful.

783
00:39:04,160 --> 00:39:06,720
If we can truly make Chengxintang paper,

784
00:39:08,680 --> 00:39:10,120
I'd die a happy man.

785
00:39:13,120 --> 00:39:13,960
Zhang Du,

786
00:39:15,280 --> 00:39:16,640
this one is one year old.

787
00:39:17,400 --> 00:39:18,880
These are two years old.

788
00:39:19,560 --> 00:39:20,640
What we need

789
00:39:21,640 --> 00:39:22,960
is over three years old.

790
00:39:25,720 --> 00:39:26,960
Use a crisp, sharp force.

791
00:39:27,000 --> 00:39:29,000
Try not to damage the bark.

792
00:39:29,280 --> 00:39:31,200
It has to sprout new buds next year.

793
00:39:33,720 --> 00:39:34,680
Here, let me.

794
00:39:45,480 --> 00:39:46,720
Chengxintang paper

795
00:39:47,000 --> 00:39:48,320
is exquisitely refined.

796
00:39:48,800 --> 00:39:50,280
From processing the raw materials,

797
00:39:50,440 --> 00:39:53,440
it demands the utmost perfection.

798
00:39:53,520 --> 00:39:55,520
After steaming the sandalwood branches,

799
00:39:55,640 --> 00:39:59,000
peel the bark as thin as noodles.

800
00:39:59,160 --> 00:40:00,520
It must be even and uniform,

801
00:40:00,640 --> 00:40:01,960
so that once the paper is made,

802
00:40:02,440 --> 00:40:04,040
the fibers will be evenly distributed.

803
00:40:21,360 --> 00:40:22,120
Master.

804
00:40:22,920 --> 00:40:25,360
Why are these screen threads so fine?

805
00:40:25,480 --> 00:40:28,680
For regular Xuan paper, one inch of screen

806
00:40:29,880 --> 00:40:30,880
of this size

807
00:40:31,080 --> 00:40:33,280
requires 31 screen threads.

808
00:40:33,520 --> 00:40:34,840
So I estimate

809
00:40:35,080 --> 00:40:37,000
the screen for Chengxintang paper

810
00:40:37,720 --> 00:40:41,280
needs at least, per inch,

811
00:40:42,000 --> 00:40:43,600
40 screen threads,

812
00:40:44,040 --> 00:40:45,400
maybe even more.

813
00:40:45,400 --> 00:40:46,680
Forty threads?

814
00:40:48,160 --> 00:40:50,000
The finer the screen,

815
00:40:50,320 --> 00:40:53,000
the smoother the paper's surface,

816
00:40:53,680 --> 00:40:55,120
and the more delicate the texture.

817
00:40:55,960 --> 00:40:57,520
That's really not easy.

818
00:40:58,040 --> 00:40:59,640
This is only the beginning.

819
00:41:01,040 --> 00:41:03,280
Xuan paper has 108 steps.

820
00:41:03,680 --> 00:41:05,280
As for Chengxintang paper,

821
00:41:06,280 --> 00:41:07,840
the hurdles it has to pass

822
00:41:07,840 --> 00:41:10,640
are definitely more than 108.

823
00:41:10,840 --> 00:41:12,800
Take the paper screen for example.

824
00:41:13,680 --> 00:41:17,720
The finer the threads,

825
00:41:18,320 --> 00:41:20,920
the softer the screen becomes.

826
00:41:21,440 --> 00:41:23,640
And the skill required of the screen handler

827
00:41:23,640 --> 00:41:24,960
becomes even more demanding.

828
00:41:25,280 --> 00:41:27,560
So to make Chengxintang paper well,

829
00:41:27,560 --> 00:41:28,640
the screen handler

830
00:41:29,560 --> 00:41:32,840
must at least shed a few layers of skin.

831
00:41:36,600 --> 00:41:37,600
I understand now.

832
00:41:38,560 --> 00:41:39,400
Mr. Xuan,

833
00:41:40,040 --> 00:41:41,560
you can rest assured about

834
00:41:41,560 --> 00:41:42,800
Dayazhai's quality control.

835
00:41:43,000 --> 00:41:44,600
From materials to craftsmanship,

836
00:41:44,880 --> 00:41:46,320
it's a complete one-to-one replica.

837
00:41:46,440 --> 00:41:47,440
No problems at all.

838
00:41:48,520 --> 00:41:49,560
That's wonderful.

839
00:41:50,360 --> 00:41:51,880
Being able to make assembly-line products

840
00:41:51,880 --> 00:41:54,000
match the design piece one-to-one,

841
00:41:54,000 --> 00:41:55,320
on this point alone,

842
00:41:56,840 --> 00:41:58,480
I have much to learn from you, Mr. Huang.

843
00:41:58,880 --> 00:42:00,920
A talented designer like you

844
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:02,320
is the true soul of the operation.

845
00:42:03,600 --> 00:42:04,320
By the way,

846
00:42:04,520 --> 00:42:06,480
I still can't believe it.

847
00:42:06,840 --> 00:42:08,880
This little booklet, palm-sized,

848
00:42:09,400 --> 00:42:10,520
can sell for several thousand.

849
00:42:11,480 --> 00:42:12,920
If I remember correctly,

850
00:42:13,000 --> 00:42:15,120
the highest auction price reached 6,800.

851
00:42:15,600 --> 00:42:17,800
None of your first batch of five products

852
00:42:17,800 --> 00:42:18,800
had an auction price

853
00:42:18,840 --> 00:42:20,280
lower than 3,000.

854
00:42:20,280 --> 00:42:22,040
And we're only selling them for 998.

855
00:42:22,840 --> 00:42:24,440
People are going to go crazy for these.

856
00:42:25,360 --> 00:42:26,120
Manager Huang,

857
00:42:26,720 --> 00:42:27,680
how's the progress?

858
00:42:28,280 --> 00:42:29,080
Don't worry, Director Xin.

859
00:42:29,400 --> 00:42:30,280
All the other production lines

860
00:42:30,280 --> 00:42:31,200
have been halted.

861
00:42:31,560 --> 00:42:32,560
The whole factory is on it.

862
00:42:32,640 --> 00:42:33,960
One thousand sets of each product

863
00:42:33,960 --> 00:42:35,800
will be produced today, guaranteed.

864
00:42:35,800 --> 00:42:36,120
Good.

865
00:42:36,680 --> 00:42:37,280
Xuan Yan,

866
00:42:37,280 --> 00:42:38,160
at 2 p.m. this afternoon,

867
00:42:38,160 --> 00:42:39,320
